    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "acd1f878_78683c2b",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/tryjobs/tryjobs.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 464,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-24T16:27:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO the best solution would be for util.ChunkIter to return a new error type util.ChunkIterError with fields for the original error and the chunk where the error occurred. If I were writing it, then in the case that there\u0027s only one chunk or the first chunk fails, I would have ChunkIterError.Error return the original error message; otherwise give details of the partial failure. (The other alternative is to return the original error when there is no partial success, but that means the caller always has to type-check the error before casting, which I don\u0027t like as much.)\n\nBut what you\u0027ve written looks fine to me. Just a little abstraction violation, but I think we\u0027re already past the point of leaky abstractions dealing with the firestore transaction doc limit.",
      "parentUuid": "05b80699_66525fe7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 458,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 464,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "e5e77616bba36d91d1bf360dea000a7e7ac5a129",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
